HEADWORD: Obese
<hw>O*bese"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>obesus</ets>
eaten away, lean; also, that has eaten itself fat, fat, stout, p. p. of
<ets>obedere</ets> to devour; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) +
<ets>edere</ets> to eat. See <er>Eat</er>.]</ety> <def>Excessively
corpulent; fat; fleshy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obeseness</ent>⟦br⟧
